          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MWPC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two large-area (120 cm2) position-sensitive",
                " multiwire proportional counters to detect fission",
                " fragments were placed at the folding angle for",
                " symmetric fission, at distances of 26 and 41 cm,",
                " respectively, from the center of the target on either",
                " side of the beam axis."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Beam flux monitoring as well as normalization",
                " by two silicon surface barrier detectors placed at",
                " +/- 10 degrees."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Four liquid-scintillator-based (BC501A) neutron",
                " detectors, each of dimension 25 inch2, were used for",
                " the detection of neutrons.",
                "The neutron detectors were placed outside the",
                " scattering chamber at angles of 30,60,90 and 120 deg",
                " at a distance of 100 cm from the target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "238U of thickness 150 ug/cm2 on 70 ug/cm2 12C backing",
                " and self-supporting 400 ug/cm2 197Au."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Time of Flight Technique.",
                "The neutron detection thresholds were kept at 100 keVee",
                " by calibrating the detectors with a standard gamma",
                " source.",
                "Neutron TOF was converted to neutron energy using a",
                " prompt gamma peak in the TOF spectrum as a time",
                " reference.",
                "The efficiency correction for the neutron detector was",
                " performed using the Monte Carlo computer code NEFF."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Fission events belonging to Gaussian centred at ~165",
                " deg were identified as fusion-fission (FF)+",
                " Quasifission (QF) events and considered for data",
                " analysis"
              ]
            }
          ],
